  "prompt": "How can I open DWG files in Adobe Illustrator?",
  "response": "To open DWG files (AutoCAD drawings) in Adobe Illustrator, you typically need to follow these steps:\n\n1. **Check Version Compatibility**: Ensure that the version of Adobe Illustrator you are using supports DWG files. Adobe Illustrator can open AutoCAD files saved in DWG format starting from version CS6 (Adobe Illustrator CS6 and later).\n\n2. **Open the DWG file**: \n   - Launch Adobe Illustrator.\n   - Go to `File` > `Open`.\n   - In the dialog box, navigate to the location of your DWG file and select it.\n   - Click `Open`. You might see an import options dialog that allows you to choose how to import the file.\n\n3. **Import Options**: If the import options dialog appears, you may be prompted to adjust settings like:\n   - Units (inches, millimeters, etc.)\n   - Scaling\n   - Layers or objects to import\n\n   Adjust these settings if needed and then click `OK`.\n\n4. **Edit the Drawing**: Once the DWG file is opened in Illustrator, you can edit it as you would any other vector graphic. Note that complex drawings may lose some fidelity or layer structure during this process.\n\n5. **Save or Export**: After making your edits, you can save the file in Illustrator format (AI) or export it to various other formats as necessary.\n\n**Troubleshooting Tips**:\n- If the file does not open, ensure that the DWG file is not corrupted and is saved in a supported version.\n- You might need additional plugins or software (like AutoCAD itself) if you encounter issues with specific features.\n\n**Converting DWG to another format**: If Illustrator has trouble opening the DWG file, consider converting the file to a different format (like DXF or SVG) using software like AutoCAD or an online converter before importing it into Illustrator.",
